Why Market Cap Matters For starters, market cap can give you a general idea of where a company stands in the business development process. It isnt necessarily the actual value of a company and all of its parts. Some of that perceived value may stem from expectations of future growth or the introduction of a product, but those expectations may not pan out, in which case the share price of the companyand thus its market capis likely to adjust accordingly.
